proof.p:
Calculate


		\inprod{\uvec{u}}{a \uvec{v}}
		\amp = \lcconj{\inprod{a \uvec{v}}{\uvec{u}}}
		\amp \amp\text{(i)}

	 \amp = \lcconj{a \inprod{\uvec{v}}{\uvec{u}}} \amp \amp\text{(ii)} 
	 \amp = \cconj{a} \lcconj{\inprod{\uvec{v}}{\uvec{u}}} \amp \amp\text{(iii)} 
	 \amp = \cconj{a} \uvecinprod{u}{v} \amp \amp\text{(iv)} 
,
with justifications



		Rule
		(or, really, Axiom CIP);



		Rule
		(or, really, Axiom CIP);



